snippet.title: Baoxiao Chuji (MS-DOS, 1992) - playthrough
snippet.description:
Baoxiao Chuji (MS-DOS, PC game, 1992) 
爆笑出擊 (爆笑出击) -- Chinese spelling 
폭소출격 - Korean spelling 

Published by Softstar Entertainment Inc. 
Developed by DOMO Production 

Baoxiao Chuji is a Taiwanese-made side-scrolling shoot-em-up. The game takes place underwater most of the time and takes a decidedly "kid-friendly" approach by replacing baddies with cute-looking monsters like octopus, clams, and other deep sea denizens. The player pilots a cute toy craft, complete with the huge winding mechanism in the back. 
https://www.mobygames.com/game/dos/baoxiao-chuji
